### Doctor-Patient Management System API Tests
### You can use the "REST Client" extension in VS Code to run these directly.
### Install it from: https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

---
### 1. Register a new Patient
# @name registerPatient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "dob": "1995-05-15",
  "password": "securepassword"
}

---
### 2. Login as Patient
# @name loginPatient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}

### Copy the token from the response above and set it here to test patient routes
@patientToken = {"{{loginPatient.response.body.token}}"}

---
### 3. Get Patient Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patients/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken}}

---
### 4. Setup Admin User (Manual DB intervention needed normally, but let's assume one exists or we login as one if seeded)
# Assuming you have an Admin account in DB
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
# Content-Type: application/json
# { "email": "admin@example.com", "password": "adminpassword" }
# @adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

---
### 5. Create a Doctor (Requires Admin Token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admins/doctors
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Smith",
  "email": "dr.smith@hospital.com",
  "specialty": "Cardiology",
  "qualifications": "MD, MBBS",
  "experience": 10,
  "fees": 500,
  "clinic": "City Heart Center",
  "gender": "Male"
}

---
### 6. Search Doctors (As Patient)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patients/doctors?specialty=Cardiology
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken}}

---
### 7. Get Admin Analytics (Requires Admin Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admins/analytics
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

---
### 8. Doctor Login (Using the temp password generated in step 5)
# @name loginDoctor
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dr.smith@hospital.com",
  "password": "TEMP_PASSWORD_FROM_STEP_5"
}

@doctorToken = {"{{loginDoctor.response.body.token}}"}

---
### 9. Doctor Changes Password 
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/password
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "TEMP_PASSWORD_FROM_STEP_5",
  "newPassword": "newsecurepassword123"
}

---
### 10. Doctor Creates a Slot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/slots
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-03-20T00:00:00.000Z",
  "startTime": "2026-03-20T10:00:00.000Z",
  "endTime": "2026-03-20T10:30:00.000Z"
}

